quantum information science the stanford photonics research center become a member member login working groups ab automotive photonics c dk entrepreneurship information technology integrated photonics lo lasers and nonlinear optics microscopy nanophotonics neuroscience ps solar cell tz quantum information science telecom ultrafast laser sources the stanford photonics research center home about research events resources membership quantum information science the qis working group develops quantum technologies with potential applications in communications computation encryption and navigation the group has been engaging industry in frank and well informed discussions of the inevitable shift to quantum technologies in many areas of information technology and telecommunications with a focus on identifying sustainable but directed strategies for bringing these quantum concepts and phenomena into commercial markets the group is exploring fundamental advances in fabrication metrology and control of nanoscale devices and understanding the quantum dynamics of these devices continuing activities of the working group will include tutorials on basic and advanced topics in quantum information science and the physics of quantum technology a moderated web discussion forum on new developments in the field and activities aimed at increasing student awareness of quantum engineering careers in industry research working groups automotive photonics entrepreneurship information technology integrated photonics lasers and nonlinear optics microscopy nanophotonics neuroscience solar cell quantum information science faculty patents presentations publications telecom ultrafast laser sources and applications stanford photonics research center ginzton laboratory ap 207 stanford university stanford ca 94305 4088 p 650 723 5627 f 650 725 1822 email photonics stanford edu stanford university terms of use stanford affiliate policy
